        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            <a href="/en/dep/bld/Press-Center/Press-releases/2008/improved-stability-for-state-funded-fost.html?id=534357" class="ISI_IGNORE">
                <img src="/upload/BLD/Temabilder/mekling_for_foreldre_150x113.jpg" alt="mekling for foreldre
mekling for foreldre" class="ArticleImg" />
            </a>
            <div class="ArticleImgContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/bld/Press-Center/Press-releases/2008/improved-stability-for-state-funded-fost.html?id=534357" title="">
                        Improved stability for state-funded foster homes
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Press release, Ministry of Children, Equality and Social Inclusion, 31.10.2008]</p>
                <p>Families that agree to provide family or emergency homes on assignment for the state will now be given new rights. New standard contracts provide these families with increased economic security, including rights to occupational pensions, paid sick leave and reimbursement of expenses for work-related injury insurance. </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                <span id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_SubjectManager_wp595570488_wp1872782628_lstSearchResult_lstUniversal_ctl06_Label1"></span>                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            <a href="/en/dep/bld/Whats-new/News/2008/nightingale.html?id=504435" class="ISI_IGNORE">
                <img src="/upload/BLD/Ingresssbilder/Standardbilder/Barnevern_100x75.jpg" alt="Nightingale" class="ArticleImg" />
            </a>
            <div class="ArticleImgContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/bld/Whats-new/News/2008/nightingale.html?id=504435" title="">
                        Nightingale
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[News story, Ministry of Children, Equality and Social Inclusion, 26.03.2008]</p>
                <p>As part of the Government’s strategy for increasing the multicultural knowledge in the child welfare service, the Ministry of Children, Equality and Social Inclusion has initiated the mentoring programme Nightingale. The programme runs at eight universities and university colleges in Norway and is funded by the Ministry of Children, Equality and Social Inclusion. </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                <span id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_SubjectManager_wp595570488_wp1872782628_lstSearchResult_lstUniversal_ctl07_Label1"></span>                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            <a href="/en/dep/bld/Press-Center/Press-releases/2007/Pre-natal-support.html?id=489535" class="ISI_IGNORE">
                <img src="/Upload/BLD/Ingresssbilder/Bufdir_100x75.jpg" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
            </a>
            <div class="ArticleImgContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/bld/Press-Center/Press-releases/2007/Pre-natal-support.html?id=489535" title="">
                        Pre-natal support
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Press release, Ministry of Children, Equality and Social Inclusion, 14.11.2007]</p>
                <p>"Children with parents who are mentally ill or who abuse alcohol or drugs must be followed closely from before birth to the start of school. We have initiated a major project in which specialized teams will guide and assist municipalities in their efforts to improve the lives of vulnerable children," says Minister of Children and Equality Manuela Ramin-Osmundsen.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                <span id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_SubjectManager_wp595570488_wp1872782628_lstSearchResult_lstUniversal_ctl08_Label1"></span>                 
           </div>
